My parents died today.

36:36.106 --> 36:38.239
There are tasks.

36:38.283 --> 36:39.719
[ Inhales deeply ]

36:39.762 --> 36:42.112
There's been, here,

36:42.156 --> 36:44.463
a peculiar concentration
of activity

36:44.506 --> 36:46.552
involving, somehow...

36:46.595 --> 36:49.032
Mexico.

36:49.076 --> 36:52.122
Among a peculiar number
of people here.

36:56.605 --> 36:59.260
Killer.

36:59.304 --> 37:00.218
Me?

37:00.261 --> 37:01.480
Yeah.

37:01.523 --> 37:02.655
Convicted.

37:02.698 --> 37:04.047
Yeah.

37:04.091 --> 37:06.659
Motherfucker taunted
my mother and father,

37:06.702 --> 37:08.095
and I did the time
behind the bars

37:08.138 --> 37:09.966
and down in the barrel.

37:10.010 --> 37:12.142
Taunted.

37:12.186 --> 37:13.579
Yeah.

37:13.622 --> 37:15.494
And you shot him.

37:15.537 --> 37:17.844
Yeah.

37:17.887 --> 37:20.281
For taunting someone.

37:20.325 --> 37:22.240
Not someone.

37:22.283 --> 37:26.635
My mother and father.

37:26.679 --> 37:28.594
And since then...

37:28.637 --> 37:32.119
Since then what?

37:32.162 --> 37:34.904
You let anyone else
have it like that?

37:34.948 --> 37:38.734
No one's given me a reason.

37:38.778 --> 37:41.911
What were you doing in Mexico,
New Leaf?

37:43.478 --> 37:44.914
New Leaf?

37:44.958 --> 37:47.656
[ Sighs ]

37:47.700 --> 37:51.138
I was researching LensCrafters
franchise opportunities

37:51.181 --> 37:53.706
in the suburbs
of Greater northwestern Mexico.

37:53.749 --> 37:56.012
I'm a registered,
licensed franchisee

37:56.056 --> 37:58.450
in the LensCrafters
franchise family.

37:58.493 --> 38:01.931
I got $96,000
of my parents' life savings

38:01.975 --> 38:03.890
laying around
in the form of hard costs,

38:03.933 --> 38:05.979
such as frames, lenses,

38:06.022 --> 38:09.243
and eyeglass stands
I'm trying to recoup on.

38:09.287 --> 38:12.507
I attended a Mexican
LensCrafters symposium yesterday

38:12.551 --> 38:15.554
for that reason.

38:15.597 --> 38:20.428
Here's my ticket,
Wesley Walker, Texas Ranger.

38:20.472 --> 38:22.778
And I was at a real fucking
disadvantage, man,

38:22.822 --> 38:25.825
seeking Mexican wholesale
franchise discount opportunities

38:25.868 --> 38:28.088
with this shit
on my ankle.

38:28.131 --> 38:30.612
So now, man...

38:30.656 --> 38:32.919
get her off.

38:32.962 --> 38:35.748
I'm not fucking around.
Look at my face.

38:41.449 --> 38:45.888
You wandered down to Mexico
with your folks at death's door?

38:45.932 --> 38:48.369
I'm useless, Ranger.

38:48.413 --> 38:49.588
It was their life savings.

38:49.631 --> 38:51.241
I endeavored
to put it to good use

38:51.285 --> 38:53.374
before they passed away
into the it's-never-gonna-

38:53.418 --> 38:55.768
fucking-happen-now
end of it all.

38:55.811 --> 38:58.379
I didn't wander
down to Mexico.

38:58.423 --> 38:59.772
I hurried.

38:59.815 --> 39:01.861
For them.

39:01.904 --> 39:03.515
Because as of 7:00 a.m.
this morning,

39:03.558 --> 39:07.127
there was still hope.

39:07.170 --> 39:08.346
And now?

39:12.306 --> 39:14.613
And now...

39:14.656 --> 39:16.354
nope.

39:21.446 --> 39:22.882
Seriously, man.

39:22.925 --> 39:25.928
Stand the fuck up
and get this off me.

39:25.972 --> 39:28.322
I got things
I need to do.

39:38.463 --> 39:44.904
♪♪

39:44.947 --> 39:51.432
♪♪

39:51.476 --> 39:54.392
Any word?

39:54.435 --> 39:55.741
Pirdoo.

39:55.784 --> 39:57.873
♪♪

39:57.917 --> 39:59.440
Word on Glenn?

39:59.484 --> 40:01.442
Word on Glenn.

40:01.486 --> 40:04.489
Glenn's home, Ranger.

40:04.532 --> 40:06.752
Well, that's great.

40:06.795 --> 40:09.494
It's fucking great, yeah.

40:09.537 --> 40:11.713
Where was your boy?

40:11.757 --> 40:13.106
Road trip.

40:13.149 --> 40:14.977
Roadie.

40:15.021 --> 40:16.457
He wrote me a note.

40:16.501 --> 40:18.851
It just washed away.

40:18.894 --> 40:21.331
He brought me
something home.

40:21.375 --> 40:22.550
From his trip?

40:22.594 --> 40:23.508
Yeah.

40:23.551 --> 40:24.900
Father's Day.

40:24.944 --> 40:26.075
Well, that's fine.

40:26.119 --> 40:27.337
[ Chuckles ]

40:27.381 --> 40:29.470
That's a fine thing.

40:29.514 --> 40:31.167
Check it out.

40:31.211 --> 40:38.479
♪♪

40:38.523 --> 40:40.133
Check it out, guy.

40:40.176 --> 40:50.491
♪♪

40:50.535 --> 41:00.762
♪♪

41:00.806 --> 41:11.120
♪♪

41:11.164 --> 41:21.435
♪♪

41:21.479 --> 41:23.524
New Leaf: Yeah,
I went to Mexico,

41:23.568 --> 41:26.571
primarily because,
if my parents passed away,

41:26.614 --> 41:30.444
I wanted to immediately
kill So-Called James.

41:30.488 --> 41:32.446
But I still, of course,

41:32.490 --> 41:35.362
frequent LensCrafters
franchise message boards

41:35.405 --> 41:38.104
in the hope of identifying
opportunities to recoup

41:38.147 --> 41:42.108
some of my parents' investment
in LensCrafters and in me.

41:42.151 --> 41:45.677
At this point,
a sweet second chance

41:45.720 --> 41:48.288
at a brick-and-mortar
franchise store is

41:48.331 --> 41:49.985
a fucking pipe dream.

41:50.029 --> 41:51.683
Who the fuck
are we kidding here,

41:51.726 --> 41:57.123
given our fiduciary situation.

41:57.166 --> 41:59.517
But it's imprudent
to bypass opportunities

41:59.560 --> 42:01.736
to allay our leftover
hard-cost stock items

42:01.780 --> 42:04.609
such as frames, lenses,
and eyeglass stands

42:04.652 --> 42:08.047
at franchise mixers and
various franchise symposiums

42:08.090 --> 42:10.963
where franchise owners
can barter, negotiate,

42:11.006 --> 42:13.531
or just do a fellow
LensCrafters franchise owner

42:13.574 --> 42:15.271
a fucking solid.

42:15.315 --> 42:16.838
So, yeah, I dropped in there.

42:16.882 --> 42:18.274
In Mexico.

42:18.318 --> 42:19.711
While there.

42:19.754 --> 42:21.669
Hoping...

42:21.713 --> 42:24.150
Hoping I could sell
some reserve stock

42:24.193 --> 42:25.978
and lessen the loss
of the investment

42:26.021 --> 42:28.110
my elderly father, Kevin,
and mother, Denise,

42:28.154 --> 42:30.417
made in LensCrafters and in me.

42:30.460 --> 42:34.073
♪♪

42:34.116 --> 42:35.901
No takers.

42:35.944 --> 42:40.470
♪♪

42:40.514 --> 42:42.124
So, at the end of their lives,

42:42.168 --> 42:44.474
what my parents lost
by investing in me

42:44.518 --> 42:46.868
was entire and full.

42:46.912 --> 42:48.478
It was complete.

42:48.522 --> 42:55.268
♪♪

42:55.311 --> 42:58.184
Now I'll just take
a bath on this shit,

42:58.227 --> 43:00.578
'cause I need
some fucking money for a gun

43:00.621 --> 43:04.669
so I can pay a fateful visit
to So-Called James.

43:04.712 --> 43:07.889
♪♪

43:07.933 --> 43:09.369
Where's young Glenn?

43:09.412 --> 43:12.590
Young Glenn is sleeping.

43:12.633 --> 43:14.243
In the back?

43:14.287 --> 43:15.810
At home.

43:15.854 --> 43:17.856
How can I help you?

43:17.899 --> 43:19.553
I got glasses.

43:19.597 --> 43:21.816
Cases and cases
of eyewear.

43:21.860 --> 43:24.036
Like, here.

43:24.079 --> 43:26.386
Cases and cases.

43:26.429 --> 43:29.345
[ Sighs ]

43:29.389 --> 43:31.565
You're gonna take a bath
on these, man.

43:31.609 --> 43:34.089
I'm not a wholesaler.
I'm a Mom-and-Pop.

43:34.133 --> 43:36.614
But my wife --

43:36.657 --> 43:39.660
my wife left us,
so I'm just a Pop.

43:39.704 --> 43:43.272
Just a Pop store, bud,
so I can't do you right, here.

43:43.316 --> 43:44.622
This is a lot of stock.

43:44.665 --> 43:47.233
Well, I need the money
for something.

43:47.276 --> 43:49.670
You own a pawn shop.
You know the story.

43:49.714 --> 43:51.672
What do you need?
We have a lot of stock.

43:51.716 --> 43:53.935
Maybe I can make you a deal
on something.

43:53.979 --> 43:55.894
You don't stock it.

43:55.937 --> 43:59.898
You don't stock
what Ineed.

43:59.941 --> 44:01.682
Well, okay.

44:01.726 --> 44:03.902
How many boxes
of eyewear?

44:03.945 --> 44:06.034
72.

44:06.078 --> 44:07.949
I'll give you $2,000,
all in.

44:07.993 --> 44:10.778
That'll cover it.

44:10.822 --> 44:12.562
[ Clears throat ]

44:12.606 --> 44:14.042
[ Pen clicks ]

44:14.086 --> 44:15.478
Hey.

44:15.522 --> 44:18.003
Yeah?

44:18.046 --> 44:20.266
You got a good kid.

44:20.309 --> 44:23.399
Your kid.

44:23.443 --> 44:25.445
I know him a little.

44:25.488 --> 44:29.014
I wanted you
to know that.

44:29.057 --> 44:31.103
Glenn?

44:31.146 --> 44:33.714
Glenn's a good kid.

44:33.758 --> 44:36.717
He is, yeah.

44:36.761 --> 44:37.979
You sure you want

44:38.023 --> 44:39.720
to follow through
on this transaction?

44:39.764 --> 44:41.853
Yeah, I am.

44:44.856 --> 44:47.249
Glenn works here?

44:47.293 --> 44:48.729
Sometimes.

44:48.773 --> 44:50.731
Most of the time.

44:50.775 --> 44:51.819
Seems like.

44:51.863 --> 44:53.821
[ Register dings ]

44:53.865 --> 44:55.910
So, it's a...

44:55.954 --> 44:59.479
more of a Kid and Pop store,
really.

44:59.522 --> 45:02.656
But no one ever says that,
'cause no one really sees that

45:02.700 --> 45:06.312
'cause kids don't really do
that that -- that much.

45:06.355 --> 45:07.835
Right?

45:10.751 --> 45:12.666
[ Register door closes ]

45:18.803 --> 45:20.282
Here's your money.

45:24.591 --> 45:32.730
♪♪

45:32.773 --> 45:42.783
♪♪

